node.text:
Join profesional climber @paigeclaassen and adventurer @naturechola as they talk all things women in climbing, social media, perfume, outdoor recreation, and everything in between! 💕👏🏾 thank you to Tio Eddie (@eddiebauer ) for co-hosting this conversation.

Happy trails! 🥾

node.text:
This is the story of Slim Pickins Outfitters (@spoutfitter), the nation’s first Black-owned outdoor gear shop, and its owners Jahmicah and Heather Dawes. Get an inside look at the inspiration behind the store, the vital energy and spirit they bring to Stephenville, TX, and the positive impact they are creating within the outdoor industry. 

PLEASE HELP SAVE SLIM PICKINS: The pandemic has had a terrible impact on Slim Pickins’ business, and we are rallying our community to help save the shop. Please join us in donating/sharing at the official GoFundMe page: http://bit.ly/saveslimpickins

This film was directed by @jusinfocus and produced by @arcticklondike. We created this film in partnership with @wondercamp.co. It is presented by @hokaoneone. It was made possible with additional support from @kampgroundsofamerica, @sawyerproducts, and @visitflorida.

#everyoneoutside #theoutbound

node.text: @lexus_is_pretty_awesome, another young leader of @outdooroutreach, has witnessed the transformative power of the outdoors. Thanks to @lesfordduncan, more and more people are gaining new perspectives after adventuring with Outdoor Outreach. Check out everyoneoutside.theoutbound.com to watch our full film about Lesford, and learn more about our mission to get #EveryoneOutside. Thanks to our partners @hokaoneone @visitflorida @kampgroundsofamerica and @eddiebauer for helping us make these films a reality.

node.text: @tati_roseb, an inspiring young leader of @outdooroutreach, has experienced the life changing wonders of exploring the outdoors. Thanks to @lesfordduncan, many more young adults from similar backgrounds to Tatiana are gaining new perspectives after adventuring with Outdoor Outreach. Check out everyoneoutside.theoutbound.com to watch our full film about Lesford, and learn more about our mission to get #EveryoneOutside. Thanks to our partners @hokaoneone @visitflorida @kampgroundsofamerica and @eddiebauer for helping us make these films a reality.

node.text:
We're excited to share the story of Lesford Duncan & Outdoor Outreach as they strive to connect youth with the transformative power of the outdoors and work to foster our next generation of leaders and advocates.

#EveryoneOutside is our initiative focused on creating a more inclusive and culturally diverse outdoor community by elevating the profiles, work, and stories of traditionally marginalized leaders and athletes.

This film was created in partnership with @wondercamp.co and is presented by @hokaoneone. It was made possible with additional support from @kampgroundsofamerica, @eddiebauer, and @visitflorida.
-
📹 @wondercamp.co
@lesfordduncan @outdooroutreach
#everyoneoutside #theoutbound

Join Teresa Baker and a group of diverse outdoor leaders as they become the first members of the public to explore the Harold Richardson Redwoods Reserve -- 700 acres of newly discovered, old growth redwood forest, protected Save the Redwoods League. Head to: http://bit.ly/EveryoneOutside to learn more!

We’re proud to have worked with @HOKAONEONE, @VisitCalifornia, @KampgroundsofAmerica, @SavetheRedwoods, and @OutdoorCEOPledge to make this film happen.

node.text:
The future of conservation is looking bright. Chris Hill, @misschrisyface is an environmentalist, angler, and lover of the outdoors. We’re excited to share our third #EveryoneOutside film that visits Chris at home in beautiful Haines, AK and explores her deep connection with outdoor spaces, the challenges she faces, her path to advocacy, and how she finds community in the outdoors. We are proud to have worked with @kampgroundsofamerica @hokaoneone and @biolite to make this film happen. Watch the full film here, and visit
http://bit.ly/EverOut
to learn more.
-
📹 @wondercamp.co #everyoneoutside #theoutbound 
@sierraclub

node.title: #EveryoneOutside Film 003: Fly Fishing with Christine Hill

node.text: Challenge accepted. Belay on. Jess Sporte, @sporteadventures, describes herself as a climber first, and a person with a disability second. She quotes “adaptive is a state of mind…not a label.” Our second #EveryoneOutside film features Jess Sporte, a climber from Golden, CO & @paradoxsports , a Boulder-based organization that provides accessible climbing experiences for people with disabilities. We are proud to have worked with @visitestespark @kampgroundsofamerica and @hokaoneone to make this film happen. Watch the full film here, and visit http://everyoneoutside.theoutbound.com to learn more.

node.title: #EveryoneOutside Film 002: Rock Climbing with Jess Sporte of Paradox Sports

node.text:
Take in the fauna and flora of this epic Idaho location by way of an epic paddling trip with some added hiking, fishing, and SUP-ing sprinkled in.⁠
⁠
All the details for your next lake excursion can be found at the link in our bio.⁠
⁠
📸 George Manlove #EveryoneOutside #TheOutbound

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Outbound Collective in Switzerland. May be an image of nature and mountain.

node.text:
You've got 1 trip to the Swiss Alps, a hankering to hike, and several options on where to go. Do you first decide whether to:⁠
⁠
A.) Hike and climb?⁠
B.) Hike to a castle?⁠
C.) Hike to a suspension bridge?⁠
D.) Hike along a glacier?⁠
⁠
Hit the link in our bio and decide for yourself where your next trek to some of the most beautiful mountains in the world will lead you.⁠
⁠
*Though this list is intended to inspire future travel plans, it's important to be aware that travel is currently being restricted in many regions. Please do your research on each place you intend to visit and #recreateresponsibly.⁠
⁠
📸 Nico Benedickt #EveryoneOutside #TheOutbound

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Outbound Collective in Bryce Canyon National Park. May be an image of nature and Bryce Canyon National Park.

node.text:
With sweeping views of towering hoodoos in sunset hues, this 5-mile out-and-back hike is beckoning you on an adventure you'll never forget.⁠
⁠
Read all about this canyon gem including trail closures/reopenings and helpful weather-related tips in our bio.⁠
⁠
📸 Tracy Zhang #EveryoneOutside #TheOutbound

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Outbound Collective in Italy. May be an image of mountain and nature.

node.text:
Need some inspiration for your next hiking trip abroad with the whole family? Experience the magic of rifugio mountain huts, partake in a yoga-hike, and meander the streets of surrounding picturesque towns.⁠
⁠
If you are contemplating hitting the button on travelling with kids in tow, this write up gives you the perfect perspective on everything you need to know to plan your next trip to the Dolomites. ⁠
⁠
*Though this list is intended to inspire future travel plans, it's important to be aware that travel is currently being restricted in many regions. Please do your research on each place you intend to visit and #recreateresponsibly.⁠
⁠
📸 @tanelah #EveryoneOutside #TheOutbound

node.text:
Known as “Hidden Lake Nature Trail”, this scenic trek takes you through meadows of wildflowers and winding switchbacks, as Clements Mountain outshines the rest of the backdrop until you make your climb down to the lake. ⁠
⁠
Read all about this easy-on-the-eyes hike in Glacier National Park in the link in our bio.⁠
⁠
📸 @noahavstin #EveryoneOutside #TheOutbound

node.text:
How do you go from backyard to frontcountry camping with small kids? We teamed up with @eddiebauer and Zenovia Stephens of @blackadventurecrew to learn from a family camping expert. 

In her guide - linked in our bio - Zenovia offers helpful tips on how to keep kids engaged during their time at camp, selecting your family's camping style, and how to meet little ones in their comfort zones for big success.

Give this guide a read for some great advice on how to get your family outside and exploring!

📸 @blackadventurecrew #EveryoneOutside #TheOutbound #OutboundSponsor #LiveYourAdventure
